Kilome MP Thuddeus Nzambia has said Kambas will deliver 100 per cent votes to Azimio One Kenya presidential candidate Raila Odinga. Nzambia said the Azimio government had lots of goodies for the community and urged residents from Lower Eastern to support Raila's bid. He lauded Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka, saying his decision rejoin Azimio will bear fruits in the best interest of the community. Nzambia spoke when he distributed National Government Constituency Development Fund bursaries at Kiongwani shopping centre in Kilome, Makueni county, on Thursday. He said Ukambani was 100 per cent locked by Wiper party. "As elected Wiper leaders, we all support Kalonzo since as a community we will benefit from more than five CSs, more than 30 ambassadors alongside several PSs,"Nzambia said. He urged the Kamba community to support Kalonzo and ensure that Raila and his running mate Martha Karua win the August 9 polls in the first round. "We thank Kalonzo for standing with the community. We will support Raila, Karua and Kalonzo to ensure they win the presidency in first round," Nzambia said. On supporting education of needy children in his constituency, Nzambia said his office had sponsored education of 301 students in secondary school since he was elected to Parliament in 2017. Nzambia said 51 of the first batch of students who received full sponsorships had joined various universities across the country. "My office has offered full sponsorships to 301 needy students in Kilome since I was elected in 2017," he said. "The first batch of those I supported their education since Form 1 have sat their KCSE examinations, and 51 qualified for university, one scored an A plain while 20 others managed A minus grades. "We will continue with educating the needy children until 2027. Let's unite so that we improve Kilome constituency's education to national standards."  (edited by Amol Awuor)